<sect1 id="dir_c44faea763af7288aeca8677f94fea29_1autotoc_md695">
<title>helios::engine::runtime::spawn::commands</title><para>Commands for spawn and despawn operations.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_c44faea763af7288aeca8677f94fea29_1autotoc_md696">
<title>Overview</title><para>This module contains command classes that represent spawn and despawn operations. These commands are emitted by systems and submitted directly to the SpawnCommandHandler during the command flush phase.</para>
<para>The system is built around <bold>compile-time type safety</bold>: command types are declared as template parameters, eliminating virtual dispatch overhead for queue access and enabling the compiler to verify command routing at build time.</para>
</sect1>
